    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="840"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d840">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">684A.85/7–354: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 840<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Jordan (<persName corresp="#p_MLD1"
                            type="from">Mallory</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d840fn1">Repeated to Tel Aviv, London, Paris, Cairo, Jidda,
                        Baghdad, Damascus, Beirut, and Jerusalem.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Amman</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-03">July 3,
                            1954</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Saw Prime Minister and conveyed substance <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 1.<note n="2" xml:id="d840fn2">
                        <ref target="#d839">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> He stated Jordan has always respected authority <gloss
                        target="#t_UNTSO1">UNTSO</gloss> and would so continue. Jordan does not wish
                    firing on border and least of all at Jerusalem and in fact it is quite against
                    her interests.</p>
                <p>He stated it would be hard to conceive of any of Jordanian initiation since the
                    Arab Legion is under British Officers. The Commander, <persName
                        corresp="#p_GLGS1">Glubb</persName>, is known for his care but to leave no
                    possibility of doubt Prime Minister had called him in to state there should be
                    no provocation and that ceasefire by fully respected.</p>
                <p>Prime Minister asked for tripartite help and appeared genuinely puzzled over
                    reason for Israeli action.</p>
                <p>Saw Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_DCB1">Duke</persName> immediately
                    thereafter. Prime Minister had made similar statement to him with the additional
                    observation that Jordan respectful of the verbal request but he believed more
                    than words would be necessary for Israel.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MLD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mallory</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
